HEADWORD: Free base
<hw>Free" base`</hw> <pr>(fr⟦emac⟧" b⟦amac⟧s`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>The basic form of an organic amine
which is capable of forming acid salts such as hydrochlorides.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The basic form of a drug, often more powerful than a
salt form because it is more readily absorbed into the blood
stream.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Free base</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>free-base</ent>⟦br⟧
